This paper deals with visual reasoning using natural language instructions, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a neural model that uses joint bidirectional attention and an RL-based pointer network, which are common techniques in computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with processing and sorting information, which is also relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
